In England, in the seven days to 16 November, there were 231,584 new confirmed cases (409.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 November, there were 194,266 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 19% (37,318 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 21 November is 8,349,363 (14,764.5 cases per 100,000 population).
